passages.text: Core Business In- Line O Strong Cyclical Trends; Strong Optical Offset 3; Lumpiness In Custom Al ASICs; We Believe Key 3nm Custom Al ASIC XPU Programs Remain On Track; Reit OW

Marvell delivered in- line Jul- Qtr results driven by upside in consumer demand that offset slightly weaker demand trends in its Data Center, Carrier Infrastructure, and Enterprise Networking businesses. For the Oct- Qtr, the team guided revenues to \(\) 2.06B\(up 3\% Q / Q), in - line with consensus if you exclude\) \ \(60M\) revenue impact from the divestiture of its automotive ethernet business. The core business (excluding the automotive Ethernet divestiture) is largely in- line, although the end market mix differs from expectations. The team expects flatish Data Center sales but a strong acceleration in Carrier Infrastructure and Enterprise Networking businesses (up \(30\% Q / Q\) ). Overall, the results and outlook are slightly weaker than we had previewed (see preview note here) as the strong Al spending trends did not translate into material upside for Marvell. Within the flatish Data Center sales outlook, the team sees double- digit \(0\% Q / Q\) growth in the optical networking business, which is being offset by lumpiness in its custom ASIC business. The team expects the custom ASIC business to re- accelerate in the Jan- Qtr and increase on a H/H basis in the 2H of the year. While management did not provide updates on Amazon's Trainium 3/4 and Microsoft MAIA 3nm/2nm programs due to strict non- disclosure/confidentiality agreements, our checks indicate that both the 3nm Trainium and 3nm Maia programs are on track for production in CY26. Looking ahead, the team continues to expand its AI ASIC design win pipeline and has secured additional sockets, on top of the 18 sockets disclosed at the analyst day. AI networking demand remains strong, driven by its 800G PAM4 DSP product, and demand for the 1.6T PAM4 DSP is beginning to ramp up, with more significant contributions expected in 2026. Overall, we believe the team's AI- related programs and products (optical/ASICs) are on track to drive a strong calendar year 2025 growth profile (up 2x year- over- year) with a strong growth profile in calendar year 2026. Overall, we see a solid setup for the company, driven by the continued recovery in its cyclical businesses and sustained AI growth tailwinds. We adjust our forward estimates, and establish our Dec- 26 PT of \(\) 120\(from our Dec - 25 PT of\) \ \(130\) . We reiterate our OW rating on MRVL.

Our Overweight thesis is based on the Marvell team's creation of a franchise that, after the close of the Inphi acquisition in April 2021, is a strong market leader in optical connectivity and will be very synergistic to Marvell's Storage (HDD/SSD controllers, Storage adapters), Networking (enterprise and cloud datacenter switching, PHY, NIC), and embedded processing (packet processing, dataplane/control plane processing, security, and encryption/algorithm acceleration) franchises.

Our Dec 2026 price target of \(\) 120\(assumes that Marvell trades at a 33x multiple applied to our\) \sim \$ 3.60 of earnings power in FY27. The P/E multiple is in - line with the company's A/Networking peers.

In- line Oct- Qtr rev outlook (ex- divested auto revenues) while core business in- line with expectations; flattish Datacenter sales (due to custom ASIC lumpiness) offset by optical and strong acceleration in cyclical segments. Revenue guidance of \(\) 2.060\(B (up\) 3\% \(Q/Q and up\) 36\% \(Y/Y) was in - line with consensus excluding the\) 60 \(million revenue impact from the divestiture of its automotive ethernet business while its core business was largely in line with expectations. The team expects flattish Data Center sales and a strong acceleration in Carrier Infrastructure and Enterprise Networking businesses. By end segment, Datacenter is expected to be flatish\) Q/Q, on double digit\% growth in optical networking demand offset by a pause in its custom ASIC business (implying double- digit\% decline). Carrier infrastructure and Enterprise Networking, in aggregate, are expected to be up\) 30\% \(Q/Q. Auto/Industrial is expected be\) 35M. Consumer is expected to be down low- single- digit\% \(Q/Q. GM guidance of\) 59.8\% \(was above consensus (\) 59.3\%) . EPS guidance of \(\) 0.74\(was slightly above consensus.

Despite near- term lumpiness in AI ASICs, we believe (based on our very recent research checks) that both the AWS Trainium 3 (3nm) and Microsoft Maia 3nm programs remain on track to ramp in CY26 setting up for a continued ramp of AI ASIC programs through next year, strong growth in AI 800G / 1.6T optical DSP shipments, and sustained recovery in cyclical businesses. The team continues to ramp production of their two AI ASIC customers (Trainium 2 and Google Axion). Overall, we believe the team's AI- related programs/products (optical/ASICs) are on track to drive a strong CY25 growth profile (up \(2x Y/Y)\) with a strong growth profile in CY26. While management did not provide updates on Amazon's Trainium 3/4 and Microsoft MAIA programs due to strict non- disclosure confidentiality, our checks indicate that these programs are on track to ramp production in CY26.

Adjusting forward estimates, and establishing our Dec- 26 PT of \(\) 120\(. We adjust our forward estimates and establish our Dec - 26 PT of\) \ \(120\) (from our Dec- 25 PT of \(\) 130\$ ). Our PT of \(\) 120\(assumes that Marvell trades at\) 33x\$ applied to \(- \\(3.60\) of earnings power in FY27.
